[{"location":"discrete/#discrete","page":"Discrete Extreme Value Models","title":"Discrete Extreme Value Models","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"continuous/#continuous","page":"Continuous Extreme Value Models","title":"Continuous Extreme Value Models","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#SpatialBayesExtremes","page":"SpatialBayesExtremes","title":"SpatialBayesExtremes","text":"The SpatialBayesExtremes package provides a collection of estimation methods for extreme events. Particularly, SpatialBayesExtremes implements:\n\nProbability-weighted moment estimation for Gumbel distribution, genralized extreme value distribution and generalized Pareto distribution\nMean excess based Hill estimation and mean excess estimator for generalized Pareto distribution\nMaximum likelihood estimation for generalized extreme value distribution and generalized Pareto distribution\nMaximum likelihood estimation for regression models, where the coefficients of generalized extreme value distribution and generalized Pareto distribution, respectively, are assumed to be linearly varying in covariates, and all samples are independent\nComing soon: Bayesian estimation for all extreme value models","category":"section"},{"location":"types/#Type-Hierarchy","page":"Type Hierarchy","title":"Type Hierarchy","text":"The extreme value models and fitted models are organized into a type hierarchy as follows:","category":"section"},{"location":"types/#Extreme-Value-Models","page":"Type Hierarchy","title":"Extreme Value Models","text":"An extreme value model provides all the information and metadata necessary to apply an estimation method, such as the parametric family, the data and covariates.","category":"section"},{"location":"types/#ExtremeValueModel","page":"Type Hierarchy","title":"ExtremeValueModel","text":"The abstract type ExtremeValueModel subsumes any types of objects which specify a parametric family meant for estimation of extremes and all necessary sample information.\n\nCurrently, we distinguish between two subtypes of ExtremeValueModel, depending on whether the model includes covariates and allows for extrapolation beyond the sample covariates (continuous) or not (discrete).\n\nabstract type DiscreteExtremeValueModel <: ExtremeValueModel end\nabstract type ContinuousExtremeValueModel <: ExtremeValueModel end","category":"section"},{"location":"types/#Fitted-Estimators","page":"Type Hierarchy","title":"Fitted Estimators","text":"The fitted estimator yields the connection between statistical model and the estimation method generating the parameter estimate.","category":"section"},{"location":"types/#FittedEstimator","page":"Type Hierarchy","title":"FittedEstimator","text":"Any type of object linking a ExtremeValueModel to a estimation method and the parameter estimates is a subtype of the abstract type FittedEstimator.\n\nabstract type FittedEstimator{M<:ExtremeValueModel} end\n\nIt has one parameter that specifies the statistical model it is the parameter estimates correspond to.","category":"section"},{"location":"types/#SpatialBayesExtremes.ExtremeValueModel","page":"Type Hierarchy","title":"SpatialBayesExtremes.ExtremeValueModel","text":"ExtremeValueModel\n\nExtremeValueModel is any type of statistical model used to represent and analyze extreme values in a dataset. Any ExtremeValueModel implements the following functions:\n\ngetDistribution\nlikelihood\nloglikelihood\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"types/#SpatialBayesExtremes.getDistribution","page":"Type Hierarchy","title":"SpatialBayesExtremes.getDistribution","text":"getDistribution(model::ExtremeValueModel,θ::NamedTuple)\n\nGet the probability distribution associated with the extreme value model given the parameters θ.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"types/#SpatialBayesExtremes.likelihood","page":"Type Hierarchy","title":"SpatialBayesExtremes.likelihood","text":"likelihood(model::ExtremeValueModel,θ::NamedTuple)\n\nCompute the likelihood of the data linked to an extreme value model given the parameters θ.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"types/#SpatialBayesExtremes.loglikelihood","page":"Type Hierarchy","title":"SpatialBayesExtremes.loglikelihood","text":"loglikelihood(model::ExtremeValueModel,θ::NamedTuple)\n\nCompute the loglikelihood of the data linked to an extreme value model given the parameters θ.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"types/#SpatialBayesExtremes.FittedEstimator","page":"Type Hierarchy","title":"SpatialBayesExtremes.FittedEstimator","text":"FittedEstimator{M<:ExtremeValueModel}\n\nAn abstract type for fitted estimators of extreme value models.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"types/#SpatialBayesExtremes.getParameterEstimate","page":"Type Hierarchy","title":"SpatialBayesExtremes.getParameterEstimate","text":"getParameterEstimate(fe::FittedEstimator)\n\nReturns the parameter estimates.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"types/#SpatialBayesExtremes.getDistributionEstimate","page":"Type Hierarchy","title":"SpatialBayesExtremes.getDistributionEstimate","text":"getDistributionEstimate(fe::FittedEstimator)\n\nReturns the probability distribution associated with the fitted estimator.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"}]
